The paper deals with stochastic optimal control in multi-agent systems, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses non-linear dynamics and control, which are topics in systems and control (cs.SY). The use of graphical models and optimization techniques suggests that the paper could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the simulations of systems with multiple agents suggest that the paper could also be classified under robotics (cs.RO).
